Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Remove the ends from the @carrot{1} (no need to peel), thinly slice into rounds. Remove the ends from the @courgette{1}, halve lengthways, chop into 2cm wide strips. Chop into 2cm chunks. Zest and halve the @lime{1/2}. Heat a #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil). Add the courgette, dry fry until nicely charred on all sides, ~{6-8%minutes} total. Turn every 2 mins. Remove to a #bowl{} once charred.

Meanwhile, pour the @water for the rice{300%ml} into a #saucepan{} and bring to the boil. When boiling, add @salt{0.25%tsp}, stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g}, lower the heat to medium and pop a lid on the pan. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Once the courgette is removed, pop your frying pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Once hot, add the @vivera plant meatballs{200%g}, fry until browned on the outside, ~{4-5%minutes}. Turn every 2 mins. Remove to a #plate{}. Pop your pan back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil if the pan is dry. Add the carrot and shallot to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry, stirring frequently until the veg is soft, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add the @red thai style paste{50%g} to the carrot and shallot. Stir well, cook for ~{1%minute}, then pour in the @coconut milk{200%ml} and @water for the sauce{100%ml}. Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and season with salt and pepper. Add the veggie meatballs back into the sauce. Bring to the boil, simmer until the sauce has thickened and the meatballs are cooked, ~{8-10%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when piping hot.

Once the curry is cooked, stir in the charred courgette and cook for ~{1%minute} to heat through.

> TIP: Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Remove the pan from the heat and squeeze in half the lime juice. Taste and add more lime juice, salt and pepper if you feel it needs it.

Fluff up the rice and stir through the lime zest. Spoon the rice into #bowls{}. Top with the curry and cut any remaining lime into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!